The elastic_integration plugin is excluded from the OSS tarball we assemble for
distribution.  However, this is done in two phases: add all the default
plugins, and then remove the `skip-oss` plugins (of which this is the only
one).  We observe Gemfile.lock related failures during that removal: this patch
means elastic_integration won't be added in the first phase, so the second
phase becomes a no-op.

diff --git a/rakelib/plugins-metadata.json b/rakelib/plugins-metadata.json
index 4684f39..1532db8 100644
--- a/rakelib/plugins-metadata.json
+++ b/rakelib/plugins-metadata.json
@@ -120,7 +120,7 @@
     "skip-list": false
   },
   "logstash-filter-elastic_integration": {
-    "default-plugins": true,
+    "default-plugins": false,
     "skip-list": false,
     "skip-oss": true
   },
